      "name": "Herbs (thyme, parsley)",
      "notes": "chopped finely"
    },
    {
      "name": "Salt and Pepper",
      "amount": "to taste"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 180°C (350°F).",
    "Mix tofu with herbs and seasonings. Place in a greased baking dish.",
    "In a separate pan, heat oil over medium-high heat. Add potato flour and stir until combined into a paste-like consistency.",
    "Pour the flour mixture evenly over the tofu layers. Bake for 25 minutes or until golden brown on top.",
    "Serve hot as a crumble or alongside toast for an Irish breakfast experience."
